original: Hultkrantz, Sigge Gustaf Emanuel, major, Göteborg, f. 22/5/88 i Åmål av godsäg. Alfred Alexander H. o. Vilhelmina Samuelsen-Schenk. G. 20 m. Astrid Bång. Barn: Göran f. 21, jur. stud., Upps., Björn 23, stud., Gbg, Erik 25, tekn. stud., Gbg, Håkan 27, stud.. Lundsberg. — Off:ex. 09, genomg. KSHS. Löjtn. v. kustart. 14, kapt. 21, major i marinen 36. Kommendant i iVlvsb. fästn. 36-39. Hobbies: ridn., tennis, jakt o. segling. RSO, Blek. skytteförb. GM, IdriGM, SkytteM, Riks sky tteM.
translated: Hultkrantz, Sigge Gustaf Emanuel, Major, Gothenburg, born May 22, 1888 in Amal to estate owner Alfred Alexander H. and Vilhelmina Samuelsen-Schenk. Married in 1920 to Astrid Bang, and had children: Goran (born 1921, studying law in Uppsala), Bjorn (born 1923, studying in Gothenburg), Erik (born 1925, studying engineering in Gothenburg), and Hakan (born 1927, studying at Lundsberg). Passed the Officer Examination in 1909 and attended the Royal Swedish Naval Staff College. Became Lieutenant in the Coastal Artillery in 1914, Captain in 1921, and Major in the Navy in 1936. Served as Commandant in Vaxholm Fortress from 1936 to 1939. Hobbies include horseback riding, tennis, hunting, and sailing. Received the Royal Order of the Sword, the Swedish National Rifle Association's gold medal, the Idrottsförbundet's gold medal, the Shooting Association's medal, and the National Shooting Medal.

awards.name: Swedish National Rifle Association's gold medal
